# Task 2 – Sequence Diagrams for API Calls

## Diagrammes

### User Registration
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
participant User
participant API
participant BusinessLogic
participant Database

User->>API: Register new account
API->>BusinessLogic: Validate & create User
BusinessLogic->>Database: Save User
Database-->>BusinessLogic: Confirm Save
BusinessLogic-->>API: Return Success
API-->>User: Registration Complete
Place Creation
Diagramme
sequenceDiagram
User->>API: Create new Place
API->>BusinessLogic: Validate & create Place
BusinessLogic->>Database: Save Place
Database-->>BusinessLogic: Confirm Save
BusinessLogic-->>API: Return Success
API-->>User: Place Created
Review Submission
Diagramme
sequenceDiagram
User->>API: Submit Review
API->>BusinessLogic: Validate & create Review
BusinessLogic->>Database: Save Review
Database-->>BusinessLogic: Confirm Save
BusinessLogic-->>API: Return Success
API-->>User: Review Submitted
Fetching List of Places
Diagramme

Notes
Chaque diagramme montre comment les couches Presentation, Business Logic et Persistence interagissent.

La facade sert d’interface unique entre l’API et les modèles.

Les opérations CRUD sont réalisées dans la couche Persistence via la base de données.


